1
00:00:30,105 --> 00:00:34,745
At his age, he doesn't need to work.
Just sit around, and that's it.

2
00:00:34,745 --> 00:00:38,305
Right. He can barely even walk now.

3
00:00:38,305 --> 00:00:40,985
You can go now.
We've come as far as we can.

4
00:01:10,355 --> 00:01:11,865
Hmph.

5
00:01:16,895 --> 00:01:17,965
Come on now.

6
00:01:37,025 --> 00:01:38,425
Your friend still not talking?

7
00:01:56,375 --> 00:02:00,285
Grandpa, are you good now?
I'm sleepy.

8
00:02:01,145 --> 00:02:02,145
Aw.

9
00:02:03,085 --> 00:02:04,585
Then go to bed, Snow.

10
00:02:07,265 --> 00:02:08,265
Okay.

11
00:02:22,405 --> 00:02:25,065
Ow...

12
00:02:26,405 --> 00:02:27,405
Ow.

13
00:02:48,865 --> 00:02:49,865
Huh.

14
00:03:46,325 --> 00:03:47,505
Ugh.

15
00:03:47,535 --> 00:03:48,535
Ouch...

16
00:03:52,225 --> 00:03:53,305
Oow.

17
00:03:55,355 --> 00:03:56,425
Ow. Ugh.

18
00:04:12,035 --> 00:04:13,545
Father's still not up?

19
00:04:16,105 --> 00:04:17,105
Father.

20
00:04:18,385 --> 00:04:19,505
You awake?

21
00:04:19,505 --> 00:04:21,585
Yeah, I'm up.

22
00:04:27,105 --> 00:04:28,345
Oh? Father.

23
00:04:36,065 --> 00:04:37,265
Are you okay?

24
00:04:40,275 --> 00:04:41,275
I'm fine.

25
00:04:41,295 --> 00:04:44,025
I just...knocked it with my hand.

26
00:04:44,465 --> 00:04:46,305
What about you? Anything wrong?

27
00:04:46,305 --> 00:04:47,505
Everything is all right.

28
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:50,825
I thought it was odd
that you weren't up yet.

29
00:04:51,025 --> 00:04:52,025
Oh, yeah, yeah.

30
00:04:53,905 --> 00:04:56,135
- I was just about to get up.
- Okay.

31
00:04:57,215 --> 00:05:00,065
Father. Oh...hmph.

32
00:05:05,145 --> 00:05:07,505
Tell me where it hurts.

33
00:05:09,945 --> 00:05:11,305
It's not that bad.

34
00:05:12,265 --> 00:05:13,825
Don't tough it out, Grandpa.

35
00:05:14,435 --> 00:05:16,675
Tell me so I'll work
on the right spots.

36
00:05:17,345 --> 00:05:18,705
My whole back is killing me.

37
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:21,005
Not just his back.

38
00:05:21,675 --> 00:05:23,895
Last night, he had me massage
his shoulders too.

39
00:05:23,985 --> 00:05:25,705
There you go.

40
00:05:26,705 --> 00:05:29,985
So where exactly does it hurt?
All of it.

41
00:05:31,105 --> 00:05:34,145
You always tell me
not to be difficult. Now you.

42
00:05:34,325 --> 00:05:36,705
Fine. Everything hurts.

43
00:05:37,185 --> 00:05:41,385
Elbow, shoulder,
the muscles, the arms...

44
00:05:43,375 --> 00:05:44,375
Let me see.

45
00:05:44,745 --> 00:05:45,945
- Oh, wow.
- Oh?

46
00:05:50,525 --> 00:05:51,525
- Dad.
- Hmm?

47
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:53,905
It's getting serious.
Let's go to a doctor.

48
00:05:54,225 --> 00:05:58,225
No, some balm and a massage will do.

49
00:05:59,335 --> 00:06:01,565
Then let's rub the balm on now.

50
00:06:01,815 --> 00:06:04,265
If it doesn't get better,
I'll take you myself.

51
00:06:08,095 --> 00:06:10,455
Hmm? What is it, Father?

52
00:06:11,055 --> 00:06:15,185
Your back brace. You done with it?
Let me use it.

53
00:06:15,215 --> 00:06:17,065
Oh, Father.

54
00:06:17,465 --> 00:06:18,615
What, Grandpa?

55
00:06:18,955 --> 00:06:22,025
You're just catching up
with the office syndrome trend.

56
00:06:24,105 --> 00:06:25,505
Come here. Let me massage you.

57
00:06:27,335 --> 00:06:28,385
Easy now.

58
00:06:28,825 --> 00:06:31,145
Gentle, son. Light pressure.
Not too hard.

59
00:06:31,175 --> 00:06:32,545
Okay, okay.
Nice and easy.

60
00:06:32,765 --> 00:06:33,795
Okay, Dad.

61
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:35,895
Ooh.

62
00:06:57,295 --> 00:06:58,295
Hey, Pipe.

63
00:07:01,035 --> 00:07:03,025
Yeah, Phi Save?
Wanna play with my doll?

64
00:07:07,585 --> 00:07:08,585
No.

65
00:07:09,505 --> 00:07:10,665
I'm here to trade.

66
00:07:12,075 --> 00:07:14,705
This one...is a secret character.

67
00:07:17,025 --> 00:07:19,745
And this one...is super rare.

68
00:07:20,905 --> 00:07:22,105
I'll give you two for it.

69
00:07:23,705 --> 00:07:25,785
Trade for this one. Deal?

70
00:07:26,985 --> 00:07:30,185
Sure, Phi Save.
Two-for-one is always a super.

71
00:07:32,705 --> 00:07:36,585
Hmm? A massage balm?
It reeks.

72
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,905
Yo, boys. New toys.

73
00:07:41,145 --> 00:07:42,265
What is it?

74
00:07:42,285 --> 00:07:43,965
- Let me see.
- Let me see.

75
00:07:43,985 --> 00:07:44,985
So cool.

76
00:07:45,015 --> 00:07:46,015
Awesome.

77
00:08:00,185 --> 00:08:01,585
"Got what you gave me."

78
00:08:01,945 --> 00:08:03,785
"It's so cute. Thanks a lot."

79
00:08:13,585 --> 00:08:15,535
"Unread message"

80
00:08:34,655 --> 00:08:37,425
Well, well...

81
00:08:37,425 --> 00:08:38,425
What?

82
00:08:39,145 --> 00:08:41,945
Don't let me catch you
sneaking up to write.

83
00:08:41,945 --> 00:08:43,175
- Hmm?
- Hehe.

84
00:08:43,595 --> 00:08:47,745
- I'm awake. Hehe.
- Hmph...back in there.

85
00:08:49,175 --> 00:08:50,545
Just rest, okay?

86
00:08:51,705 --> 00:08:54,985
So? You patched things up
with him yet?

87
00:08:59,225 --> 00:09:01,665
Sounds like he's cut you
out of his life.

88
00:09:02,265 --> 00:09:03,545
Think so?

89
00:09:03,545 --> 00:09:04,545
Well,...

90
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:07,025
you went at him pretty hard first.

91
00:09:09,295 --> 00:09:10,295
Yeah.

92
00:09:10,975 --> 00:09:12,155
I messed up. I know.

93
00:09:12,525 --> 00:09:14,545
Oh-ho. Ho.

94
00:09:15,545 --> 00:09:16,545
Look at you.

95
00:09:17,065 --> 00:09:19,385
It took you long enough

96
00:09:19,745 --> 00:09:23,425
to admit you were wrong, huh?

97
00:09:24,055 --> 00:09:26,985
That big ego?
I must have gotten it from you.

98
00:09:28,585 --> 00:09:31,505
Then how about
trying a little harder?

99
00:09:33,935 --> 00:09:34,935
Like how?

100
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:38,035
Make him something.

101
00:09:38,905 --> 00:09:39,985
Handmade.

102
00:09:40,015 --> 00:09:43,375
Correct. Hey, a story for ya.

103
00:09:43,745 --> 00:09:45,465
I once made a friend angry.

104
00:09:45,785 --> 00:09:48,305
I made something for him.

105
00:09:48,405 --> 00:09:51,385
It's a gun box. He was into guns.

106
00:09:51,905 --> 00:09:55,145
The moment he saw it,
he lit right up.

107
00:09:55,865 --> 00:09:56,885
Ah-ha.

108
00:09:57,835 --> 00:10:00,285
But...I don't know
how to make anything.

109
00:10:01,325 --> 00:10:03,285
- Can I just buy something?
- No.

110
00:10:03,865 --> 00:10:05,195
When you make it yourself,

111
00:10:05,945 --> 00:10:09,185
he'll see how much
you really mean it.

112
00:10:09,455 --> 00:10:11,265
And the harder it is to make,

113
00:10:11,745 --> 00:10:16,585
the more he'll know
you're truly sorry.

114
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:19,535
Got it, Grandpa.

115
00:10:22,985 --> 00:10:25,425
Thanks so much. I'll be back.

116
00:10:25,445 --> 00:10:26,735
Yeah...

117
00:10:26,755 --> 00:10:27,905
You rest.

118
00:10:28,875 --> 00:10:31,785
Hmm...rest, okay? I'll be back.

119
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:09,985
"'Geez, how can I
make peace with Nan now?'"

120
00:11:10,545 --> 00:11:15,825
"He mutters and vents
to the empty room."

121
00:11:16,465 --> 00:11:18,585
"'I shouldn't have run
my mouth like that.'"

122
00:11:18,805 --> 00:11:21,445
"The young man
going back and forth,"

123
00:11:21,555 --> 00:11:24,025
"thinking of a way to
make things right with his friend."

124
00:11:24,345 --> 00:11:28,265
"He hopes to restore the friendship,
the way it used to be."

125
00:11:31,685 --> 00:11:33,545
"DIY gift, hardest to make"

126
00:11:39,515 --> 00:11:40,655
Knitting.

127
00:11:46,745 --> 00:11:48,875
"Easiest knit craft"

128
00:11:50,135 --> 00:11:51,135
No, no. Wrong.

129
00:11:54,325 --> 00:11:56,025
What is the...

130
00:11:57,115 --> 00:11:59,385
hardest thing to knit?

131
00:12:02,765 --> 00:12:03,985
Knit a sweater.

132
00:12:04,965 --> 00:12:05,965
Let's do it.

133
00:12:07,075 --> 00:12:08,105
Huh.

134
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:16,585
- There you are.
- Ah.

135
00:12:16,615 --> 00:12:18,335
