Your novel or not,

268
00:21:48,455 --> 00:21:50,525
he's someone I want to keep around.

269
00:21:51,705 --> 00:21:53,425
That means you care about Guy a lot.

270
00:21:53,985 --> 00:21:54,985
Care? No way.

271
00:21:55,135 --> 00:21:59,225
Your story's got my hands itching.

272
00:21:59,245 --> 00:22:01,245
I really want to
get back to writing.

273
00:22:01,275 --> 00:22:04,705
Right now, you need rest.
Or your back will get worse.

274
00:22:04,795 --> 00:22:08,275
But the ideas are flooding my head.

275
00:22:09,345 --> 00:22:12,585
You have to take care of your body.

276
00:22:12,845 --> 00:22:14,015
For a writer like you,

277
00:22:14,365 --> 00:22:19,025
your fingers, wrists,
arms, back, and shoulders

278
00:22:19,845 --> 00:22:21,905
do need your attention.
You know that?

279
00:22:22,485 --> 00:22:24,385
They're your bread and butter.

280
00:22:24,515 --> 00:22:26,075
- Yeah, look at that.
- Ouch.

281
00:22:26,095 --> 00:22:26,835
Haha.

282
00:22:26,855 --> 00:22:29,825
Coming from the guy
who just kicked a tree.

283
00:22:30,535 --> 00:22:33,545
Come on, Grandpa. Trust me on this.

284
00:22:33,945 --> 00:22:37,425
Some manga artists
push themselves so hard

285
00:22:37,705 --> 00:22:39,445
they have to take a year off.

286
00:22:40,065 --> 00:22:42,385
Take care of yourself,
then get back on the novel.

287
00:22:45,565 --> 00:22:48,285
Getting old. Everything's a hassle.

288
00:22:49,855 --> 00:22:52,765
Have you tried this app
on your phone?

289
00:22:52,785 --> 00:22:55,025
You just speak
and it writes for you.

290
00:22:55,465 --> 00:22:58,265
No. I like reading
my own handwriting.

291
00:22:58,865 --> 00:23:01,865
What about recording?
You can capture a lot of ideas.

292
00:23:02,075 --> 00:23:04,465
No. Can't go back
and edit a recording.

293
00:23:04,865 --> 00:23:06,025
Grandpa.

294
00:23:06,845 --> 00:23:09,415
Just pick something.
Do whatever works for now.

295
00:23:09,625 --> 00:23:11,075
Fine. Fine, I'll do it.

296
00:23:12,665 --> 00:23:13,665
Your phone.

297
00:23:17,295 --> 00:23:18,295
Alright.

298
00:23:20,105 --> 00:23:22,745
Right here. Press here.

299
00:23:25,225 --> 00:23:26,785
Hello, check, check.

300
00:23:26,965 --> 00:23:27,965
Done.

301
00:23:29,665 --> 00:23:31,225
"Hello, check, check."

302
00:23:31,225 --> 00:23:33,345
Hey, that's not hard at all.

303
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:35,545
See? Told you.

304
00:23:36,865 --> 00:23:37,865
What's in that bag?

305
00:23:39,545 --> 00:23:40,545
This?

306
00:23:47,995 --> 00:23:50,425
I'm just...following your advice.

307
00:24:32,565 --> 00:24:33,565
Ow.

308
00:24:35,185 --> 00:24:38,025
Ugh, why is this so hard?

309
00:24:41,945 --> 00:24:42,945
Come on.

310
00:25:04,785 --> 00:25:05,985
'I'm sorry,'

311
00:25:09,945 --> 00:25:11,145
Somporn says.

312
00:25:11,545 --> 00:25:15,145
The guilt was written
all over those eyes.

313
00:25:18,985 --> 00:25:20,185
I'm sorry.

314
00:25:20,465 --> 00:25:21,625
Don't bother.

315
00:25:22,905 --> 00:25:25,705
If you meant what you did,
don't apologize.

316
00:25:28,975 --> 00:25:31,525
Man, it was just a moment of anger.

317
00:25:31,925 --> 00:25:34,185
I promise it won't happen again.

318
00:25:42,555 --> 00:25:45,665
I know you like dogs.
Carved this for you all night.

319
00:25:49,535 --> 00:25:50,535
You didn't clean it?

320
00:25:51,285 --> 00:25:53,135
Uhm...I did a little.

321
00:26:41,305 --> 00:26:42,625
Not mad anymore?

322
00:26:43,875 --> 00:26:44,875
Still am.

323
00:27:19,665 --> 00:27:23,215
Yo, guys,
any good spot to study tonight?

324
00:27:23,505 --> 00:27:25,665
There's a cafe near my place.
Open 24 hours.

325
00:27:25,665 --> 00:27:26,665
Cool.

326
00:27:28,185 --> 00:27:29,465
Guy, Save, you two coming?

327
00:27:31,675 --> 00:27:34,185
They got into uni already.
They don't care.

328
00:27:34,545 --> 00:27:35,545
Yeah.

329
00:27:36,895 --> 00:27:37,895
I'll go.

330
00:27:39,535 --> 00:27:41,695
Guy, come with us.

331
00:27:44,475 --> 00:27:46,345
I'm busy. You guys go.

332
00:27:49,175 --> 00:27:51,385
Hey, what's going on with you two?

333
00:27:52,345 --> 00:27:54,105
Seriously, are you two in a fight?

334
00:27:54,475 --> 00:27:55,475
- No.
- No.

335
00:27:57,935 --> 00:27:59,055
Both of you, come here.

336
00:27:59,795 --> 00:28:01,715
- Get up.
- Come here.

337
00:28:01,735 --> 00:28:02,735
Get up.

338
00:28:08,025 --> 00:28:10,025
Guys, excuse us, please.

339
00:28:23,865 --> 00:28:26,865
Alright, you talk.
We'll handle this.

340
00:28:30,145 --> 00:28:33,465
Dudes, this awkward vibe.
It's killing us.

341
00:28:33,825 --> 00:28:36,385
Any beef between you two,
just let it out. Come on.

342
00:28:38,865 --> 00:28:40,025
Ask Save yourself.

343
00:28:49,205 --> 00:28:51,115
Yeah, I was the one
who made him mad.

344
00:28:52,025 --> 00:28:53,905
When I tried to make up,
he wouldn't.

345
00:28:54,745 --> 00:28:55,785
Try him, will ya?

346
00:28:56,145 --> 00:28:57,385
What did you do to him?

347
00:29:04,845 --> 00:29:06,385
Is it about me teasing you guys?

348
00:29:07,745 --> 00:29:08,745
No.

349
00:29:08,785 --> 00:29:10,145
So what is it about then?

350
00:29:19,865 --> 00:29:22,805
Look, if you can't talk
with us around,

351
00:29:23,825 --> 00:29:25,105
then just the two of you.

352
00:29:26,065 --> 00:29:28,105
If you can't work it out,
don't come out.

353
00:29:28,925 --> 00:29:29,925
We go, guys.

354
00:29:42,805 --> 00:29:43,985
I've got nothing to say,

355
00:29:46,145 --> 00:29:47,345
except sorry.

356
00:29:48,785 --> 00:29:50,225
That's all you've got?

357
00:29:51,145 --> 00:29:52,665
It's what I genuinely feel.

358
00:30:00,535 --> 00:30:01,535
Guy.

359
00:30:02,625 --> 00:30:04,145
Can we give this another shot?

360
00:30:09,045 --> 00:30:11,825
All this time, you were just
playing around.

361
00:30:12,305 --> 00:30:14,145
I was the only one who was serious.

362
00:30:15,585 --> 00:30:16,945
I should just let you go.

363
00:30:17,465 --> 00:30:19,105
I don't want to fall any deeper.

364
00:30:52,465 --> 00:30:53,465
Hmm.

365
00:30:57,755 --> 00:30:58,825
Ow.

366
00:31:05,995 --> 00:31:06,995
Oow.

367
00:31:09,105 --> 00:31:10,105
Hrr.

368
00:31:13,485 --> 00:31:14,485
Oops.

369
00:31:17,155 --> 00:31:18,155
Hmm.

370
00:31:21,845 --> 00:31:23,265
Hey.

371
00:31:31,285 --> 00:31:32,455
Grr.

372
00:31:34,395 --> 00:31:36,105
Good thing nothing's broken.

373
00:31:36,945 --> 00:31:38,185
- Ouch.
- Easy, easy.

374
00:31:38,595 --> 00:31:39,865
Sorry, sorry.

375
00:31:40,485 --> 00:31:41,545
Serves you right.

376
00:31:41,895 --> 00:31:44,225
Told me not to work.

377
00:31:44,615 --> 00:31:50,135
Now you're the one who barely slept.
Dang near wiped out on that bike.

378
00:31:50,355 --> 00:31:51,145
That teach ya?

379
00:31:51,195 --> 00:31:53,065
Aw, Dad.

380
00:31:53,645 --> 00:31:56,665
I've got bones of steel.
Gonna hit me hard to finish me off.

381
00:31:56,715 --> 00:31:57,865
Hehe.

382
00:31:59,535 --> 00:32:00,535
Ow.

383
00:32:01,275 --> 00:32:03,585
Oh. Ow.

384
00:32:03,605 --> 00:32:06,545
Look at this.
We're all down for the count.

385
00:32:07,945 --> 00:32:09,785
Is this a home or a hospital?

386
00:32:12,425 --> 00:32:13,285
Huh.

387
00:32:13,305 --> 00:32:17,025
And today Auntie Oui called in
to run some errands.

388
00:32:17,325 --> 00:32:18,465
What do we do now?

389
00:32:26,145 --> 00:32:29,665
Alright. Watch your six.

390
00:32:30,305 --> 00:32:31,465
Watch your six.

391
00:32:31,465 --> 00:32:32,465
Be careful.

392
00:32:32,835 --> 00:32:34,385
Hey, food's coming.

393
00:32:35,235 --> 00:32:36,545
Jedi, slow down.

394
00:32:37,775 --> 00:32:38,945
Put them right here.

395
00:32:39,935 --> 00:32:40,935
Whew. That was a workout.

396
00:32:42,335 --> 00:32:43,335
Let's see.

397
00:32:44,335 --> 00:32:47,185
Okay, line up. Quick.

398
00:32:49,085 --> 00:32:50,085
Hmph.

399
00:32:51,065 --> 00:32:51,885
Quick.

400
00:32:51,905 --> 00:32:53,585
- Yeah...
- Get in line.

401
00:33:01,115 --> 00:33:03,095
Okay. Okay.

402
00:33:05,225 --> 00:33:06,465
Pipe, hurry up.

403
00:33:08,105 --> 00:33:09,585
- Okay, go.
- Got it.

404
00:33:09,615 --> 00:33:10,745
Just a sec.

405
00:33:11,885 --> 00:33:13,805
Here you go.

406
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:14,825
Come, come.

407
00:33:15,385 --> 00:33:16,205
Thank you.

408
00:33:16,225 --> 00:33:17,985
Enjoy your meal.

409
00:33:18,265 --> 00:33:21,105
- Please enjoy.
- Thank you.

410
00:33:21,625 --> 00:33:22,665
- Water.
- Get water.

411
00:33:22,915 --> 00:33:26,145
Wow, I wouldn't have guessed

412
00:33:26,525 --> 00:33:28,355
the kids would make
fried rice and egg.

413
00:33:28,625 --> 00:33:29,905
They did.

414
00:33:30,795 --> 00:33:32,005
You didn't help, did you?

415
00:33:32,065 --> 00:33:36,915
How could I?
Even moving hurts right now.

416
00:33:38,225 --> 00:33:43,625
Kids these days are smarter
than we give them credit for.

417
00:33:46,645 --> 00:33:48,305
Yeah, good stuff.

418
00:33:58,425 --> 00:34:01,745
Hi, everyone. Will you throw
this guy some support?

419
00:34:01,745 --> 00:34:05,265
With these Sanae Chan sweets,
you're gonna love them.

420
00:34:05,265 --> 00:34:06,305
You won't be disappointed.

421
00:34:06,585 --> 00:34:07,865
"Where is Phi Guy?"

422
00:34:10,305 --> 00:34:11,645
Have you ordered yet?

423
00:34:11,885 --> 00:34:13,465
Try one box.

424
00:34:14,065 --> 00:34:15,305
And you'll love them.

425
00:34:20,705 --> 00:34:23,345
And...any questions, just ask.

426
00:34:24,465 --> 00:34:27,545
Order now. They look amazing.
Super delicious. I promise.

427
00:35:04,395 --> 00:35:07,145
All this time, you were just
playing around.

428
00:35:07,585 --> 00:35:09,565
I was the only one who was serious.

429
00:35:09,735 --> 00:35:11,155
I think I should just let go.

430
00:35:11,745 --> 00:35:13,345
I don't want to fall any deeper.

431
00:35:40,505 --> 00:35:41,585
Ugh.

432
00:35:58,185 --> 00:36:03,585
Somporn yearned to
make things right with Nan.

433
00:36:04,225 --> 00:36:08,265
Something was slowly taking shape,

434
00:36:08,865 --> 00:36:11,185
like...a whirlpool.

435
00:36:11,825 --> 00:36:15,865
"Even though Nan kept
that cold, stiff wall up,"

436
00:36:18,985 --> 00:36:20,565
"in one unguarded moment,"

437
00:36:20,945 --> 00:36:23,905
"their eyes locked for just
a fraction of a second,"

438
00:36:24,705 --> 00:36:28,585
"and Somporn knew instantly that..."

439
00:36:29,225 --> 00:36:34,905
"Nan wanted the same thing."

440
00:36:36,665 --> 00:36:39,995
His eyes gave it away.

441
00:36:52,795 --> 00:36:56,345
Hmph.

442
00:37:00,175 --> 00:37:01,175
Grandpa.

443
00:37:12,205 --> 00:37:13,205
Grandpa.

444
00:37:14,985 --> 00:37:15,985
Grandpa.

445
00:37:19,625 --> 00:37:20,625
Ow.

446
00:37:49,645 --> 00:37:51,905
- Hello.
- Hello.

447
00:37:52,545 --> 00:37:56,225
Ma'am, these are Sanae Chan sweets
by Auntie Mart.

448
00:37:56,225 --> 00:37:59,345
This is a royal court recipe,
with a Japanese twist,

449
00:37:59,345 --> 00:38:01,105
because it uses mochi flour.

450
00:38:01,235 --> 00:38:04,845
That gives it a chewy texture
unlike anything else.

451
00:38:04,865 --> 00:38:07,945
- They're flying off the shelves.
- Yes.

452
00:38:08,205 --> 00:38:12,605
- If you buy now, you got a three...
- get 1 free deal.

453
00:38:12,605 --> 00:38:15,185
Price? Just as sweet.
Super wallet-friendly.

454
00:38:15,215 --> 00:38:17,495
Just 60 baht a box.

455
00:38:18,425 --> 00:38:20,065
Let's do a taste test.

456
00:38:20,065 --> 00:38:22,165
- 3, 2, 1.
- 3, 2, 1.

457
00:38:22,625 --> 00:38:23,625
Ting.

458
00:38:24,625 --> 00:38:26,065
- Yum.
- Oh.

459
00:38:26,705 --> 00:38:30,145
- So good. Unbelievable texture.
- Soft and chewy like a dream.

460
00:38:30,145 --> 00:38:31,665
Nothing else comes close.

461
00:38:57,825 --> 00:38:58,825
Come in.

462
00:39:05,985 --> 00:39:07,145
Here you go.

463
00:39:41,295 --> 00:39:42,825
"5"

464
00:40:40,385 --> 00:40:42,315
"Between Us in the Deep Forest"

465
00:40:42,315 --> 00:40:43,945
Give it a read for me.

466
00:41:05,865 --> 00:41:09,185
"Lacerating yearn" means what?

467
00:41:10,265 --> 00:41:11,545
You don't know that word?

468
00:41:12,665 --> 00:41:14,225
Tell us, Director.

469
00:41:14,505 --> 00:41:15,705
It means what, Grandpa?

470
00:41:18,665 --> 00:41:21,225
Simply put, it means
to miss someone.

471
00:41:21,445 --> 00:41:24,345
But on a deeper level.

472
00:41:24,665 --> 00:41:25,345
Hmm?

473
00:41:25,345 --> 00:41:27,145
So deep it burns.

474
00:41:27,145 --> 00:41:28,065
- Woo.
-Hoo.

475
00:41:28,065 --> 00:41:29,825
Wanting to see that face every day.

476
00:41:29,825 --> 00:41:30,825
- Heh.
- Sweet.

477
00:41:31,065 --> 00:41:35,385
Wanting to hold them,
wanting them near always.

478
00:41:35,385 --> 00:41:37,185
- Argh.
- Raah.

479
00:41:38,255 --> 00:41:41,505
Yes, you've hit the sweet spot.
Perfect.

480
00:41:41,585 --> 00:41:42,305
Yes.

481
00:41:42,305 --> 00:41:45,745
I love it so much, Grandpa.
Is there more? Please, please.

482
00:41:46,025 --> 00:41:47,225
Yes.

483
00:41:48,245 --> 00:41:49,425
I need to read more.

484
00:41:56,025 --> 00:41:58,385
So? Fun, right?

485
00:41:58,985 --> 00:42:00,065
So much fun, sir.

486
00:42:00,505 --> 00:42:03,265
So your publishing house
will print it for me?

487
00:42:04,545 --> 00:42:06,905
Yes, the writing is beautiful.

488
00:42:06,905 --> 00:42:07,465
Mm-hmm.

489
00:42:07,465 --> 00:42:08,985
- The style is great.
- Yes.

490
00:42:09,315 --> 00:42:11,225
But it's a bit much
for young readers.

491
00:42:11,635 --> 00:42:12,635
Not at all.

492
00:42:12,865 --> 00:42:16,105
The kids at my place read it
and all understood it fine.

493
00:42:16,705 --> 00:42:20,745
And to make sure,
we can explain in footnotes.

494
00:42:20,885 --> 00:42:24,625
So readers who don't know
the vocabulary can learn as they go.

495
00:42:26,625 --> 00:42:27,825
Here's the thing, sir.

496
00:42:28,105 --> 00:42:30,825
I'm not saying
it's not a good novel.

497
00:42:31,985 --> 00:42:35,225
But I'm not sure it'll sell
in the current market.

498
00:42:35,225 --> 00:42:38,185
I think it's a bit niche.
It's not...quite mass.

499
00:42:38,705 --> 00:42:39,705
Mass?

500
00:42:40,225 --> 00:42:42,105
Meaning it won't appeal to many.

501
00:42:43,185 --> 00:42:46,945
And like I mentioned before,
it needs NC scenes.

502
00:42:47,825 --> 00:42:51,065
But yours maxes out at a hug.

503
00:42:52,715 --> 00:42:53,715
Hmm.

504
00:42:55,065 --> 00:42:56,345
My suggestion, sir.

505
00:42:57,085 --> 00:43:00,305
Maybe try submitting it
elsewhere first.

506
00:43:00,665 --> 00:43:01,905
I'm rooting for you.

507
00:43:37,825 --> 00:43:38,865
Huh.

508
00:43:41,625 --> 00:43:45,425
It's okay, Grandpa.
They can't see it, but I can.

509
00:43:49,825 --> 00:43:51,505
We don't need a publisher anymore.

510
00:43:53,345 --> 00:43:54,345
I have a way.

511
00:43:57,315 --> 00:44:00,465
These days,
people post novels online.

512
00:44:01,065 --> 00:44:02,425
People publish on their own.

513
00:44:02,425 --> 00:44:04,545
You can do an e-book
or a print copy.

514
00:44:05,585 --> 00:44:06,985
Does that cost a lot?

515
00:44:07,125 --> 00:44:10,625
Posting online is free.

516
00:44:11,465 --> 00:44:14,265
But if you want a print copy,
I will chip in.

517
00:44:15,935 --> 00:44:17,025
You have money?

518
00:44:17,305 --> 00:44:20,525
Sold some game accounts.
Got a decent amount.

519
00:44:20,545 --> 00:44:24,705
You actually make money
tapping on your phone all day?

520
00:44:24,705 --> 00:44:26,705
Hmm, not bad, huh?

521
00:44:27,955 --> 00:44:31,905
But...how can I take your money?

522
00:44:31,905 --> 00:44:32,905
No.

523
00:44:33,795 --> 00:44:37,905
Grandpa, I want to use it
to help our family.

524
00:44:42,795 --> 00:44:45,255
Oh, don't cry.

525
00:44:46,505 --> 00:44:48,745
Ooh...I'm not crying.

526
00:44:52,245 --> 00:44:53,245
Now.

527
00:44:54,105 --> 00:44:55,105
Here.

528
00:44:57,705 --> 00:45:01,105
And Grandpa, I paid someone
to design a cover.

529
00:45:01,885 --> 00:45:02,945
Nice, isn't it?

530
00:45:03,545 --> 00:45:05,025
- Really nice.
- Mm-hmm.

531
00:45:05,765 --> 00:45:07,965
And if I upload this now,

532
00:45:08,345 --> 00:45:10,345
by tomorrow, it may be out. Perfect.

533
00:45:10,345 --> 00:45:12,745
It's a holiday.
People will have time to read.

534
00:45:15,075 --> 00:45:18,115
So...what pen name do you want?

535
00:45:18,865 --> 00:45:19,905
Harn Chanprai?

536
00:45:19,935 --> 00:45:21,455
Hmm? No, no.

537
00:45:22,665 --> 00:45:24,025
Then what?

538
00:45:24,705 --> 00:45:26,795
Anything. Help me think of one.

539
00:45:27,455 --> 00:45:29,985
Something people won't
trace back to me.

540
00:46:02,305 --> 00:46:03,305
Yeah.

541
00:46:03,665 --> 00:46:05,545
Save, get over here now. Right now.

542
00:46:06,295 --> 00:46:07,295
What's going on?

543
00:46:08,305 --> 00:46:09,505
Guy's leaving today.

544
00:46:09,875 --> 00:46:12,865
Today? Why? Where's he going?

545
00:46:14,485 --> 00:46:17,025
America on an athletic scholarship.

546
00:46:17,585 --> 00:46:19,825
We're at the school field.
Get here fast.

547
00:46:27,905 --> 00:46:30,265
Grandpa, I have to run.

548
00:46:30,665 --> 00:46:31,825
Have Snow come help, okay?

549
00:46:32,345 --> 00:46:33,345
Okay?

550
00:46:48,635 --> 00:46:49,635
Ow.

551
00:46:52,865 --> 00:46:55,455
- Where are you rushing off to?
- I'll borrow the bike, Dad.

552
00:46:55,625 --> 00:46:59,345
Sure, ride carefully.
I just had it fixed.

553
00:47:00,715 --> 00:47:01,985
Where's he going?

554
00:47:31,915 --> 00:47:35,065
Save, jeez, you took forever.

555
00:47:35,185 --> 00:47:36,185
Where's Guy?

556
00:47:36,385 --> 00:47:37,245
He already left.

557
00:47:37,245 --> 00:47:38,185
What?

558
00:47:38,185 --> 00:47:39,695
Didn't you pass him on the way?

559
00:47:49,505 --> 00:47:50,505
Guy.

560
00:47:54,185 --> 00:47:55,185
Guy.

561
00:47:59,225 --> 00:48:00,345
I made you something.

562
00:48:09,105 --> 00:48:10,145
You did this yourself?

563
00:48:11,625 --> 00:48:12,625
Yeah.

564
00:48:12,905 --> 00:48:13,905
I don't want it.

565
00:48:14,275 --> 00:48:15,275
Just take it.

566
00:48:16,275 --> 00:48:18,075
Don't turn down a gift, man.

567
00:48:19,695 --> 00:48:21,105
Use it as a rag if you want.

568
00:48:21,385 --> 00:48:22,865
We're parting ways, right?

569
00:48:23,765 --> 00:48:24,885
What do you mean?

570
00:48:25,305 --> 00:48:26,625
You're leaving today.

571
00:48:27,505 --> 00:48:28,505
Leaving where?

572
00:48:28,745 --> 00:48:29,745
America.

573
00:48:30,905 --> 00:48:31,905
What America?

574
00:48:38,985 --> 00:48:39,985
Forget it.

575
00:48:41,425 --> 00:48:42,505
I want you to have it,

576
00:48:43,145 --> 00:48:44,495
know that I'm sorry,

577
00:48:45,555 --> 00:48:46,905
and consider it my apology.

578
00:48:47,545 --> 00:48:49,425
You don't want us anymore,

579
00:48:51,585 --> 00:48:52,785
that's okay.

580
00:48:54,145 --> 00:48:55,705
But can we go back to how we were?

581
00:49:05,385 --> 00:49:08,505
You told me things can't go back
to the way they were.

582
00:49:10,545 --> 00:49:11,545
Forget it.

583
00:49:24,025 --> 00:49:25,025
Okay.

584
00:49:26,905 --> 00:49:28,155
So you don't want my apology

585
00:49:29,585 --> 00:49:30,945
or to be friends?

586
00:49:31,835 --> 00:49:32,835
Mm-hmm.

587
00:50:06,785 --> 00:50:10,025
Pipe, hurry up. Big mission today.

588
00:50:10,025 --> 00:50:11,865
I'm already walking fast.

589
00:50:12,295 --> 00:50:15,135
Hmph. I get stuck on duty with you
of all people?

590
00:50:15,745 --> 00:50:17,225
It's not like I like this.

591
00:50:17,865 --> 00:50:18,865
Whatever.

592
00:50:21,965 --> 00:50:22,965
Hey.

593
00:50:23,385 --> 00:50:24,385
What?

594
00:50:25,425 --> 00:50:26,665
It's blooming.

595
00:50:36,905 --> 00:50:37,905
Oh...

596
00:50:53,045 --> 00:50:56,305
Grandpa, please help me.

597
00:51:10,505 --> 00:51:13,025
Come on everyone, quickly.

598
00:51:13,465 --> 00:51:14,745
Come here, this way.

599
00:51:14,775 --> 00:51:17,185
- Go, go.
- Grandpa, here.

600
00:51:20,715 --> 00:51:23,445
Here, I checked the auspicious time.

601
00:51:23,755 --> 00:51:26,605
At 8 AM sharp, you hit publish.

602
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:29,865
- Oh wow, she came prepared.
- Oh...

603
00:51:29,865 --> 00:51:30,985
Trust me on this.

604
00:51:30,985 --> 00:51:31,985
Got it.

605
00:51:39,195 --> 00:51:40,505
7:59.

606
00:51:41,975 --> 00:51:42,975
Hey.

607
00:51:43,505 --> 00:51:44,505
It's up, everyone.

608
00:51:44,535 --> 00:51:46,385
- Yeah.
- Yay.

609
00:51:48,825 --> 00:51:49,825
Hmm...

610
00:51:52,365 --> 00:51:53,365
Hey, one.

611
00:51:53,395 --> 00:51:57,505
- Yeah.
- Yes.

612
00:51:57,505 --> 00:51:58,505
Everyone.

613
00:51:59,095 --> 00:52:02,185
